<br>
please give me more credit than thinking i'm talking about a damage shield....  i tend to think i speak for myself in such a way that people would think of me a little bit mroe than that, but i guess not..... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umandari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mandari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/1/01 10:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: force fields</span><hr size=1> I read the message clearly, and you're right (I've considered the same notion).  Reasonable, but exploitable, even if it's a two way shield (it can't harm us, we can't harm it).  A Group Force Barrier that acted as a group rune effect seems more reasonable.  Of course, to be balancing the damage absorption couldn't be too high (remember, VI thinks our personal shields absorb just the right amount of damage), worth at most one round of combat by mobs of that level.  And, no doubt, it would cost a reagent or two.<br>
<br>
But nothing wrong with stretching our imaginations in search of new tricks; Verant certainly hasn't.<br>
<br>
